{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"## Changes","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084029388Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084036211Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"### 1. Default args for known agents (`prompt.go:21-25`)","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084039827Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"Added default arguments for `gemini` and `codex` so users can switch agents by just changing `agent_command = \"gemini\"` without needing to specify `agent_args`:","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084058723Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- **gemini**: `-p` (prompt from stdin)","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084074363Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- **codex**: `-q --approval-mode full-auto` (quiet mode, auto-approve)","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084079232Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084087908Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"### 2. Fixed race condition in step executor (`runner.go:135-153`)","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084092607Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"The old code mutated the shared `prompt.Adapter` when applying per-step `agent_command`/`agent_args` overrides. If two agent steps ran in parallel (via fanout wiring), they'd stomp on each other. Now `promptAdapterForStep()` creates a shallow copy with overrides instead of mutating the shared instance.","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.0840996Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084112946Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"### 3. Fallback attempt logging (`prompt.go:96-108`)","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084116402Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"When a fallback occurs, the adapter now logs messages via `StatusWriter`:","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084129457Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- `[fallback] agent \"claude\" failed, trying \"gemini\"` — when switching","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084135238Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- `[fallback] agent \"gemini\" succeeded` — when a fallback agent succeeds","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084144455Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084153743Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"### 4. Empty-output exit-0 is now fallback-eligible (`prompt.go:244-248`)","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084161798Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"Previously, if an agent exited 0 but produced no output (common with auth/API key issues), it returned an error immediately. Now it's treated as fallback-eligible, so the next agent in the chain gets tried.","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084166958Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084177117Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"### 5. Exported `ArgsFor` method (`prompt.go:46`)","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084182517Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"Renamed `argsFor` → `ArgsFor` to make it testable from `_test` package.","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084191835Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-07T16:38:02.084201042Z"}
